theorem Topology.P1_iUnion {ι : Sort*} {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    (A : ι → Set X) (hP1 : ∀ i, Topology.P1 (A := A i)) :
    Topology.P1 (A := Set.iUnion A) := by
  dsimp [Topology.P1] at hP1 ⊢
  intro x hx
  rcases mem_iUnion.1 hx with ⟨i, hxAi⟩
  have hx_closure_i : x ∈ closure (interior (A i)) := (hP1 i) hxAi
  have h_subset : closure (interior (A i)) ⊆
                  closure (interior (⋃ j, A j)) := by
    have h_int_subset : interior (A i) ⊆ interior (⋃ j, A j) := by
      have hA_subset : (A i : Set X) ⊆ ⋃ j, A j :=
        subset_iUnion _ i
      exact interior_mono hA_subset
    exact closure_mono h_int_subset
  exact h_subset hx_closure_i

theorem Topology.closure_subset_closureInterior_of_P2
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA : Topology.P2 (A := A)) :
    closure A ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
  -- `P2` implies `P1`, giving `A ⊆ closure (interior A)`.
  have hP1 : Topology.P1 (A := A) := Topology.P2_implies_P1 hA
  have h_subset : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A) := hP1
  -- Taking closures preserves inclusions.
  simpa [closure_closure] using closure_mono h_subset
